title: Saltus Philomusianus
description: Saltus Philomusianus was a sizable imperial estate located between Bulla Regia and Chimtou. Roman soldiers of legio III Augusta seem to have garrisoned a praesidium in the estate ca. 52-57 CE.

properties.description: 1:500,000 scale representative point location digitized from the Barrington Atlas of the Greek and Roman World by the Digital Atlas of Roman and Medieval Civilizations project at Harvard University.
